HEADWORD: Paraphimosis
<hw>Par`a*phi*mo"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/; <?/ beyond + <?/ to muzzle.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
condition in which the prepuce, after being retracted behind the glans
penis, is constricted there, and can not be brought forward into place
again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

